---

<Layout title={guideData.title} description={guideData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best AI website builder for fitness professionals?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For personal trainers and fitness coaches, Mixo ($9/month) is the best choice with affordable pricing, booking forms, client testimonials, and service pages perfect for showcasing training packages. Wix works well for gyms and fitness centers needing booking apps, class schedules, membership management, and payment processing through its extensive app marketplace. Squarespace excels for yoga and pilates studios with beautiful presentation, class schedules, booking integration, and serene aesthetic that matches wellness brands. Framer is ideal for online fitness coaches wanting modern aesthetic (9.5/10), program showcases, video integration, and marketing landing pages. For fitness websites, prioritize: clear booking and scheduling, membership/pricing information, class schedules, instructor profiles, client testimonials and transformations, location details, and mobile optimization for on-the-go bookings."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do fitness professionals need custom websites or are AI builders sufficient?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "AI website builders are absolutely sufficient for 95% of fitness professionals. Modern AI builders create professional fitness websites with booking systems, class schedules, payment processing, membership management, and all key features. Integrations with Calendly, Acuity, Stripe, and other fitness tools work seamlessly with AI builders. Consider custom development only if you have: very complex membership systems, custom app development needs, integration with proprietary fitness software, or substantial budget. For personal trainers, yoga studios, gyms, and fitness coaches, AI builders provide professional results at a fraction of the cost and time. Your clients care about your expertise, training quality, and results - not website technology. Focus on: clear offerings, easy booking, social proof, and professional presentation. AI builders handle all of this beautifully."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What features should fitness websites include?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Fitness websites need: (1) Clear service offerings and pricing - personal training, classes, packages, memberships, (2) Booking and scheduling system - Calendly, Acuity, or built-in booking, (3) Class schedule for studios - weekly timetable with descriptions and booking, (4) Instructor/trainer profiles - photos, credentials, specialties, personalities, (5) Client testimonials and transformations - success stories with photos (with permission), (6) Location and parking information - map, address, access details, (7) Contact information and consultation booking, (8) About section with your fitness philosophy and approach, (9) New member information - what to expect, what to bring, (10) Social media links - Instagram, YouTube for fitness content, (11) Mobile-optimized booking experience, (12) Video content - facility tour, workout demos, instructor intros. key: make booking easy, showcase results, display clear pricing, provide comprehensive information. Your website exists to convert visitors into bookings and memberships."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I handle bookings and scheduling on fitness websites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For bookings, you have three main approaches. (1) Built-in booking - Wix Bookings, Squarespace Scheduling, and Acuity Scheduling (Squarespace acquisition) integrate directly. Handle everything on your platform, track clients, process payments, send reminders. Best for personal trainers and studios wanting simplicity. (2) Third-party integration - Calendly works with all AI builders, provides powerful scheduling features, free tier available, but requires visitors to leave your site. Best for consultants offering varied session types. (3) Custom forms + manual - Mixo, Webflow, or Framer forms collect booking requests, then you manually confirm and schedule. Lowest cost but most labor. For 1-on-1 personal trainers: Calendly or built-in booking. For class-based studios: Wix Bookings or Squarespace Scheduling with class management. For online coaches: custom forms work fine since you're handling scheduling manually anyway."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What membership and payment features do fitness websites need?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Membership and payment needs vary by fitness business type. Personal trainers: need payment processing for single sessions and training packages. Stripe integration (available on all AI builders) handles this. No recurring membership needed typically. Gyms and studios: need recurring memberships, class packages, drop-in pricing. Wix and Squarespace have built-in membership and e-commerce for this. Consider specialized platforms like Mindbody only if you have complex multi-location needs. Online coaches: need recurring subscription billing for programs. Stripe or Square handle recurring payments on any AI builder. Critical payment features: secure payment processing (Stripe standard), automatic receipts and invoices, failed payment handling, membership cancellation process, refund policy clearly stated. Display pricing prominently - hidden costs kill conversions. Offer multiple tiers (single, package, unlimited) to capture different budget levels."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I showcase client transformations and testimonials effectively?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Client transformations are your most powerful marketing asset. Get written permission for all photos - create a simple release form. Tell the full story: before photo with stats (weight, measurements), after photo with same stats, timeline (8 weeks, 6 months), their approach (training 3x/week, nutrition changes), their results. This context makes transformations credible and inspiring. Video testimonials are even more powerful than photos. Use Squarespace or Webflow for beautiful before/after galleries. Mixo works fine for simpler testimonial layouts. Critical: include their name and photo for authenticity - anonymous testimonials lack credibility. Rotate testimonials regularly to show fresh results. Feature your best transformations prominently on your homepage. Case studies with detailed client stories outperform simple before/after photos by 40% in conversion tests."
        }
      },
