          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "General AI builders are sufficient for most fitness professionals and offer significant advantages: lower cost (Mixo at $9/mo vs Mindbody at $129/mo), more design control, better customization, no vendor lock-in. Specialized fitness platforms (Mindbody, Trainerize) make sense only if you need: complex multi-studio management, dedicated fitness apps for clients, advanced workout programming and tracking, integration with specific gym equipment. For personal trainers, yoga studios, and gyms with simple needs, AI builders + Stripe + Calendly provide everything at 10% of the cost. The tradeoff: you'll need to assemble integrations yourself, but the savings justify the effort. Consider hybrid approach: start with AI builder for cost savings, migrate to specialized platform only when scale justifies the expense. Most fitness professionals never outgrow AI builders."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

